# STACK RULE

Always follow the stack and conventions already used by this repository unless the user explicitly requests a change.

## Required behavior
- Reuse the existing framework, language, folder structure, and coding style
- Reuse existing components, hooks, services, utils, routing, and state patterns when possible
- Preserve existing APIs, page structure, and integration patterns when possible
- Keep changes minimal, focused, and compatible with the current codebase

## H5 project expectations
- Prefer React + TypeScript
- Prefer the current UI library and existing page/component patterns
- Prefer the current request wrappers, service layer, route conventions, and state handling already used in the repository
- Reuse existing Less/CSS/styled patterns already used in the project
- For embedded WebView pages, prefer compatibility-safe implementations and avoid unnecessary browser-only features

## Avoid
- Do not introduce new libraries unless truly necessary
- Do not migrate frameworks or rewrite unrelated modules
- Do not replace the existing UI library or styling approach without explicit request
- Do not change route structure, API contracts, or shared component behavior unless required by the task

## Delivery preference
- Keep code directly usable in the current project
- Finish related imports, types, event wiring, and integration code in the same run when obvious
- Prefer consistent project style over personal preference
